        <link rel="schema.DC" href="https://purl.org/DC/elements/1.0/" /><meta name="citation_journal_title" content="RadioGraphics" /><meta name="dc.Title" content="Three-dimensional Automated Breast US: Facts and                    Artifacts" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Ingolf  Karst" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Christopher  Henley" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Nadine  Gottschalk" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Sara  Floyd" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Ellen                            B.  Mendelson" /><meta name="dc.Description" content="Familiarity with common patterns of automated breast US artifacts and their causes can help radiologists reduce preventable false-positive recommendations and increase efficiency." /><meta name="Description" content="Familiarity with common patterns of automated breast US artifacts and their causes can help radiologists reduce preventable false-positive recommendations and increase efficiency." /><meta name="dc.Description" content="As automated breast (AB) US becomes more integrated into the daily practice of breast imaging, the need to address the artifacts that interfere with AB US image interpretation is becoming more impo..." /><meta name="Description" content="As automated breast (AB) US becomes more integrated into the daily practice of breast imaging, the need to address the artifacts that interfere with AB US image interpretation is becoming more impo..." /><meta name="dc.Publisher" content=" Radiological Society of North America " /><meta name="dc.Date" scheme="WTN8601" content="2019-05-31" /><meta name="dc.Type" content="research-article" /><meta name="dc.Format" content="text/HTML" /><meta name="dc.Identifier" scheme="manuscript" content="180104" /><meta name="dc.Identifier" scheme="doi" content="10.1148/rg.2019180104" /><meta name="dc.Identifier" scheme="url" content="https://doi.org/10.1148/rg.2019180104" /><meta name="dc.Source" content="https://doi.org/10.1148/rg.2019180104" /><meta na